  "url": "https://www.linkedin.com/posts/honzajavorek_python-africa-namibia-activity-7032007586929344513-xtqn?utm_source=combined_share_message&utm_medium=member_desktop&rcm=ACoAABsRci0Bys2i3dGvj01b19crqhDpGozYwSA",
  "timeSincePosted": "3yr",
  "shareUrn": "urn:li:share:7032007585297784832",
  "text": "Are you a fan of the #Python programming language? 🐍 Are you thrilled by the thought of how successful #Africa could be if given the right opportunities? 🚀 And do you have some spare ~500 CZK? 💰 I can recommend a perfect cause you can support with this money! 💸\n\nIn just a few days, my dearest PyCon Namibia takes place. You may not be able to attend this year, it's probably too late for that, but you can still support their cause! Individual ticket starts around ~500 CZK.\n\nI've visited na.pycon.org in 2020, right before all the covid mayhem. It was a life-changing experience which I totally recommend if you're into exploring the world's PyCons. Not only for the touristic aspect of visiting #Namibia 🇳🇦 and its deserts, but mainly because at #PyConNA, I've met the truest people ❤️\n\nI can assure you that the organizers of this conference, led by Ngazetungue Muheue and Jessica Upani, put the purest intentions in everything they do. With very little resources they're able to make insane impact in their community. I know them personally from both my trip to Namibia and their recent visit to #UbuntuSummit, Prague.\n\nI bought a ticket for this year's na.pycon.org myself, and I told Muheue to give it to someone who needs it. It would make my day if I convinced at least one person by this status to buy a ticket too, so that they have a bit more resources to continue with their programming activities for students, getting computer labs for kids, and organizing Python events 🥲\n\nPlease, let me know in the comment, if you do buy a ticket to support them. It would really make me super happy!",
